C2X function

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| C2X(string)                                                                 |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+

Returns a hexadecimal string (i.e., composed of the characters 0-9 and A-F)
where each character in the input string is expanded to its EBCDIC
representation in hexadecimal.

Examples:

	C2X('72s')   == 'F7F2A2'
	C2X('0123'x) == '0123'
